cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with routing in overlay networks. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the proposed algorithm is distributed. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper uses the dual subgradient descent method, which is a technique from optimization and control theory. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with optimizing throughput. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the paper proposes a routing algorithm to improve the performance of the underlay network.
